# (git 4) Analysis II (<i>d<sub>XY</sub></i> & pi)

This pipeline can be executed as follows:

```sh
cd $BASE_DIR/nf/04_analysis_dxy
source ../sh/nextflow_alias.sh
nf_run_dxy
```

## Summary

The genetic divergence, as well diversity, are computed within the [**nextflow**](https://www.nextflow.io/) script `analysis_dxy.nf` (located under `$BASE_DIR/nf/04_analysis_dxy/`).
It takes the _all BP_ data set and computes $d_{XY}$ and $\pi$.
Below is an overview of the steps involved in the analysis.
(The <span style="color:#4DAF4A">green dot</span> indicates the genotype input, <span style="color:#E41A1C">red arrows</span> depict output that is exported for further use.)

## Details of `analysis_dxy.nf`

### Data preparation

The nextflow script starts by opening the genotype data and feeding it into two different streams (one for _d<sub>XY</sub>_ and one for $\pi$).

<div class="kclass">

<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode">#<span class="hl opt">!/</span>usr<span class="hl opt">/</span>bin<span class="hl opt">/</span>env nextflow
<span class="hl slc">// This pipeline includes the analysis run on the</span>
<span class="hl slc">//   all callable sites data sheet (dxy).</span>

<span class="hl slc">// git 4.1</span>
<span class="hl slc">// load genotypes</span>
<span class="hl kwa">Channel</span>
	.fromFilePairs<span class="hl opt">(</span><span class="hl str">&quot;../../1_genotyping/3_gatk_filtered/filterd.allBP.vcf.{gz,gz.tbi}&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.into<span class="hl opt">{</span> vcf_ch<span class="hl opt">;</span> vcf_pi_ch <span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

The computation of _d<sub>XY</sub>_ is split by linkage group, so we need to initialize a channel for the LGs.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 4.2</span>
<span class="hl slc">// initialize LGs</span>
<span class="hl kwa">Channel</span>
	.from<span class="hl opt">( (</span><span class="hl str">&#39;01&#39;</span>..<span class="hl str">&#39;09&#39;</span><span class="hl opt">) + (</span><span class="hl str">&#39;10&#39;</span>..<span class="hl str">&#39;19&#39;</span><span class="hl opt">) + (</span><span class="hl str">&#39;20&#39;</span>..<span class="hl str">&#39;24&#39;</span><span class="hl opt">) )</span>

### <i>d<sub>XY</sub></i>

To prepare all species comparisons used to estimate divergence, we combine each species witch all other species within a location.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 4.7</span>
<span class="hl slc">// prepare pair wise dxy</span>
<span class="hl slc">// ------------------------------</span>
<span class="hl slc">// create all possible species pairs depending on location</span>
<span class="hl slc">//   and combine with genotype subset (for the respective location)</span>
<span class="hl slc">// ------------------------------</span>
<span class="hl slc">// channel content after joining:</span>
<span class="hl slc">// set [0:val(loc), 1:file(vcf), 2:file(pop), 3:val(spec1), 4:val(spec2)]</span>
<span class="hl slc">// ------------------------------</span>
bel_pairs_ch <span class="hl opt">=</span> <span class="hl kwa">Channel</span>.from<span class="hl opt">(</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;bel&quot;</span> <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span> bel_spec1_ch <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span> bel_spec2_ch <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.filter<span class="hl opt">{</span> it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">1</span><span class="hl opt">] &lt;</span> it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">3</span><span class="hl opt">] }</span>
	.map<span class="hl opt">{</span> it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">0</span><span class="hl opt">,</span><span class="hl num">2</span><span class="hl opt">,</span><span class="hl num">4</span><span class="hl opt">]}</span>
hon_pairs_ch <span class="hl opt">=</span> <span class="hl kwa">Channel</span>.from<span class="hl opt">(</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;hon&quot;</span> <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span> hon_spec1_ch <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span>hon_spec2_ch<span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.filter<span class="hl opt">{</span> it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">1</span><span class="hl opt">] &lt;</span> it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">3</span><span class="hl opt">] }</span>
	.map<span class="hl opt">{</span> it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">0</span><span class="hl opt">,</span><span class="hl num">2</span><span class="hl opt">,</span><span class="hl num">4</span><span class="hl opt">]}</span>
pan_pairs_ch <span class="hl opt">=</span> <span class="hl kwa">Channel</span>.from<span class="hl opt">(</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;pan&quot;</span> <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span> pan_spec1_ch <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span>pan_spec2_ch<span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.filter<span class="hl opt">{</span> it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">1</span><span class="hl opt">] &lt;</span> it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">3</span><span class="hl opt">] }</span>
	.map<span class="hl opt">{</span> it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">0</span><span class="hl opt">,</span><span class="hl num">2</span><span class="hl opt">,</span><span class="hl num">4</span><span class="hl opt">]}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

Now we attach the genotypes and the resolution level to the species pairs.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 4.8</span>
<span class="hl slc">// combine species pair with genotypes (and window size)</span>
bel_pairs_ch
	.concat<span class="hl opt">(</span> hon_pairs_ch<span class="hl opt">,</span> pan_pairs_ch <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span> geno_ch <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span> kb_ch <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.into <span class="hl opt">{</span> all_dxy_pairs_ch<span class="hl opt">;</span> random_dxy_pairs_ch <span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

At this point, we can calculate <i>d<sub>XY</sub></i>.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 4.9</span>
<span class="hl slc">// compute the dxy values</span>
<span class="hl kwa">process</span> dxy_lg <span class="hl opt">{</span>
	<span class="hl kwb">label</span> <span class="hl str">&#39;L_G32g15h_dxy_lg&#39;</span>

	<span class="hl kwb">input</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl kwa">set</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> loc <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> spec1 <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> spec2 <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> lg <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> vcf <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> geno <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> kb <span class="hl opt">)</span> <span class="hl kwa">from</span> all_dxy_pairs_ch

	<span class="hl kwb">output</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl kwa">set</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;</span><span class="hl ipl">${spec1}${loc}</span><span class="hl str">-</span><span class="hl ipl">${spec2}${loc}</span><span class="hl str">-</span><span class="hl ipl">${kb}</span><span class="hl str">&quot;</span> <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;dxy.</span><span class="hl ipl">${spec1}${loc}</span><span class="hl str">-</span><span class="hl ipl">${spec2}${loc}</span><span class="hl str">.LG</span><span class="hl ipl">${lg}</span><span class="hl str">.</span><span class="hl ipl">${kb}</span><span class="hl str">0kb-</span><span class="hl ipl">${kb}</span><span class="hl str">kb.txt.gz&quot;</span> <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> lg <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;</span><span class="hl ipl">${spec1}${loc}</span><span class="hl str">&quot;</span> <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;</span><span class="hl ipl">${spec2}${loc}</span><span class="hl str">&quot;</span> <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> kb <span class="hl opt">)</span> <span class="hl kwa">into</span> dxy_lg_ch

	<span class="hl kwb">script</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl str">&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
<span class="hl str">	module load openssl1.0.2</span>
<span class="hl str">	module load intel17.0.4 intelmpi17.0.4</span>
<span class="hl str"></span>
<span class="hl str">	zcat</span> <span class="hl ipl">${geno}</span> <span class="hl str">| \</span>
<span class="hl str">		head -n 1 | \</span>
<span class="hl str">		cut -f 3- | \</span>
<span class="hl str">		sed &#39;s/</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">t/</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">n/g&#39; | \</span>
<span class="hl str">		awk -v OFS=&#39;</span><span class="hl esc">\\</span><span class="hl str">t&#39; &#39;{print \$1, substr( \$1, length(\$1) - 5, 6)}&#39; &gt; pop.txt</span>
<span class="hl str"></span>
<span class="hl str">	mpirun \$NQSII_MPIOPTS -np 1 \</span>
<span class="hl str">		python \$SFTWR/genomics_general/popgenWindows.py \</span>
<span class="hl str">		-w</span> <span class="hl ipl">${kb}</span><span class="hl str">0000 -s</span> <span class="hl ipl">${kb}</span><span class="hl str">000 \</span>
<span class="hl str">		--popsFile pop.txt \</span>
<span class="hl str">		-p</span> <span class="hl ipl">${spec1}${loc}</span> <span class="hl str">-p</span> <span class="hl ipl">${spec2}${loc}</span> <span class="hl str">\</span>
<span class="hl str">		-g</span> <span class="hl ipl">${geno}</span> <span class="hl str">\</span>
<span class="hl str">		-o dxy.</span><span class="hl ipl">${spec1}${loc}</span><span class="hl str">-</span><span class="hl ipl">${spec2}${loc}</span><span class="hl str">.LG</span><span class="hl ipl">${lg}</span><span class="hl str">.</span><span class="hl ipl">${kb}</span><span class="hl str">0kb-</span><span class="hl ipl">${kb}</span><span class="hl str">kb.txt.gz \</span>
<span class="hl str">		-f phased \</span>
<span class="hl str">		--writeFailedWindows \</span>
<span class="hl str">		-T 1</span>
<span class="hl str">    &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>

	<span class="hl kwb">tag</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;</span><span class="hl ipl">${pop1[0]}</span><span class="hl str">-</span><span class="hl ipl">${pop2[0]}</span><span class="hl str">&quot;</span>

	<span class="hl kwb">input</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl kwa">set</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> comp <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> dxy <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> lg <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> pop1 <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> pop2 <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> kb <span class="hl opt">)</span> <span class="hl kwa">from</span> tubbled_dxy

	<span class="hl kwb">script</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>

</div>

For control, we also create a "random" <i>d<sub>XY</sub></i> run, where we take the most diverged species pair and randomize the population assignment of the samples.
Therefore, we first pick the most diverged species pair.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 4.12</span>
<span class="hl slc">// collect a species pair to randomize</span>
<span class="hl kwa">Channel</span>
	.from<span class="hl opt">( [[</span><span class="hl str">&#39;bel&#39;</span><span class="hl opt">,</span> <span class="hl str">&#39;ind&#39;</span><span class="hl opt">,</span> <span class="hl str">&#39;may&#39;</span><span class="hl opt">]] )</span>
	.set<span class="hl opt">{</span> random_run_ch <span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

Then we set the sliding window resolution.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// git 4.13</span>
<span class="hl slc">// setup channel content for random channel</span>
<span class="hl kwa">Channel</span>
	.from<span class="hl opt">(</span> <span class="hl num">1</span> <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span> random_run_ch <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span> kb_ch2 <span class="hl opt">)</span>
	.filter<span class="hl opt">{</span> it<span class="hl opt">[</span><span class="hl num">4</span><span class="hl opt">] ==</span> <span class="hl num">5</span> <span class="hl opt">}</span>
	.set<span class="hl opt">{</span> random_sets_ch <span class="hl opt">}</span>
</code>
</pre>
</div>

Now, we randomize the population assignment of the samples and calculate differentiation.

### $\pi$

Estimating the diversity is quite straight forward:
We take the prepared population identifier, the data set and the window resolutions and run `VCFtools` on each combination.


<div class="sourceCode">
<pre class="sourceCode">
<code class="sourceCode"><span class="hl slc">// ---------------------------------------------------------------</span>
<span class="hl slc">// The pi part need to be run AFTER the global fst outlier</span>
<span class="hl slc">// windows were selected (REMEMBER TO CHECK FST OUTLIER DIRECTORY)</span>
<span class="hl slc">// ---------------------------------------------------------------</span>

<span class="hl slc">// git 4.19</span>

	<span class="hl kwb">tag</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;</span><span class="hl ipl">${spec}</span><span class="hl str">&quot;</span>
	<span class="hl kwb">publishDir</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;../../2_analysis/pi/</span><span class="hl ipl">${kb}</span><span class="hl str">0k&quot;</span><span class="hl opt">,</span> mode<span class="hl opt">:</span> <span class="hl str">&#39;copy&#39;</span>

	<span class="hl kwb">input</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
	<span class="hl kwa">set</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> spec <span class="hl opt">),</span> vcfId<span class="hl opt">,</span> <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> vcf <span class="hl opt">),</span> <span class="hl kwc">val</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> kb <span class="hl opt">)</span> <span class="hl kwa">from</span> spec_dxy.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span> vcf_pi_ch <span class="hl opt">)</span>.combine<span class="hl opt">(</span> kb_ch3 <span class="hl opt">)</span>

	<span class="hl kwb">output</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>
   <span class="hl kwc">file</span><span class="hl opt">(</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;*.</span><span class="hl ipl">${kb}</span><span class="hl str">0k.windowed.pi.gz&quot;</span> <span class="hl opt">)</span> <span class="hl kwa">into</span> pi_50k

	<span class="hl kwb">script</span><span class="hl opt">:</span>

<span class="hl str">		--window-pi-step</span> <span class="hl ipl">${kb}</span><span class="hl str">000 \</span>
<span class="hl str">		--out</span> <span class="hl ipl">${spec}</span><span class="hl str">.</span><span class="hl ipl">${kb}</span><span class="hl str">0k 2&gt;</span> <span class="hl ipl">${spec}</span><span class="hl str">.pi.log</span>

<span class="hl str">		--out</span> <span class="hl ipl">${spec}</span><span class="hl str">_no_outlier.</span><span class="hl ipl">${kb}</span><span class="hl str">0k 2&gt;</span> <span class="hl ipl">${spec}</span><span class="hl str">_</span><span class="hl ipl">${kb}</span><span class="hl str">0k_no_outllier.pi.log</span>

At this step we are done with divergence and diversity.

---
